-- S.Africa's Steinhoff to buy Pepkor stake in $5.7 bln deal
-- By Helen Nyambura-Mwaura
-- Tue Nov 25, 2014 02:15AM EST
-- None



JOHANNESBURG, Nov 25 (Reuters) - South African furniture retailer Steinhoff International <SHFJ.J> will acquire a 92 percent stake in clothing retailer Pepkor in a 62.8 billion rand ($5.7 billion) deal that will give it exposure to the fast-growing apparel market.

